UID:TODO-DC3C5552-FAB3-443A-B2CA-6CB44B796516
DTSTAMP:20260422T192822Z
SUMMARY:DH & ADH [@dhmtg]
DESCRIPTION:1. Courses:\n   1. AC and GT thought to have each course approv
 ed by the CCC.\n   2. HB said already too much time spent on Curriculum Pl
 ans\; better\n      to ask faculty their suggestions to make a core list. 
  Then\n      exceptions could be handled by CCC.\n2. Curriculum Cmte Oral 
 Exams\n   1. Lesser "volunteered" himself\, but maybe we need a process?\n
    2. Crosby suggested an examiner bank for each exam.\n   3. ☑ For next f
 aculty meeting:\n      • keep separate from Curriculum changes (Tew).\n   
    • prepare slide with context of current students "in process"\n        
 1. C+ in POLYMER 604: self-study\, continue with 704.  Oral\n           ex
 am at the end of Spring 2026 semester on 604 subject\n           matter.  
 Grade in 704 will also be considered as part of\n           demonstrating 
 proficiency.\n        2. C+ in POLYMER 604: audit undergraduate courses in
  Fluid\n           Mechanics and in Statics.  Oral exam at the end of Fall
 \n           2026 semester on 604 subject matter.  Proceed with\n         
   POLYMER 704 in Spring 2027 semester.\n        3. C+ in POLYMER 607: audi
 t POLYMER 501 for the chemistry\n           portion and take the correspon
 ding exam.  Grade in 760\n           will also be considered as part of de
 monstrating\n           proficiency.\n      • options for examiners\; open
  floor for discussion\n        1. Cmte selects both examiners\; potentiall
 y both prior\n           instructors.  Student has no agency.\n        2. 
 Cmte presents a list of possible examiners.  Student can\n           choos
 e one.  Cmte selects the other.\n        3. Collectively establish an exam
 iner "bank" to rotate among\n           faculty members.  Potential for su
 bject matter mismatch.\n3. +Independent Study in POLYMER+\n   1. Time-sens
 itive\, but bottleneck with Groth handling everything.\n   2. Undergrad Pr
 ogram Director (Ribbe) to handle?  Access in SPIRE?
CATEGORIES:@dhmtg,AssocDH
SEQUENCE:1
PRIORITY:5
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
END:VTODO
